I"ø<p>Anxiety can be triggered as a response to a threat to our attachment needs for safety and connection.</p>

<p>Everybody has attachment needs such as love, connection and acceptance. When we do not feel secure in our relationships our in our environments, anxiety is a natural alarm system that exists as a coping mechanism to tell us something is wrong.</p>

<p>If we are experiencing a conflict or rupture in our relationships, this may trigger anxiety as a signal that our needs are threatened.</p>
